# REQUIRED. The API refuses to boot without these. No public-repo fallback.
# Generate each with: `openssl rand -hex 32`
#   JWT_SECRET          — HS256 signing key for session cookies + Telegram link intents.
#   ENCRYPTION_KEY      — master passphrase for per-row AES-256-GCM envelope
#                         encryption of Mudrex / webhook secrets.
#   FINGERPRINT_SECRET  — HMAC key used by the legacy Mudrex-secret login
#                         endpoint to find an existing row without storing the
#                         plaintext secret. Required only when `/api/auth/login`
#                         is reachable; required in prod since we do not gate
#                         legacy login. After you set it, the API auto-backfills
#                         `user_secret_fingerprint` on first boot (no Railway shell
#                         needed). `npm run script:backfill-user-fingerprint` is
#                         optional for manual re-runs.
# Rotating any of them is disruptive:
#   - JWT_SECRET rotation signs everyone out.
#   - ENCRYPTION_KEY rotation invalidates every stored Mudrex / webhook secret.
#   - FINGERPRINT_SECRET rotation requires re-running the backfill script
#     (`npm run script:backfill-user-fingerprint`) before flipping the env var.
# Dev-only escape hatch (never set in production): REXALGO_ALLOW_DEV_SECRETS=1
# makes a missing value fall back to a tagged fake so `next dev` boots.
JWT_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-string
ENCRYPTION_KEY=change-me-use-a-strong-random-passphrase
FINGERPRINT_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-hex-string

# Google sign-in: must match the SPA's VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID (OAuth client id).
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Optional mass sign-out (stateless JWT cookies): reject session tokens issued before this Unix time (seconds).
# Set in Railway to `date +%s`, redeploy the API — everyone must sign in with Google again. Unset to stop enforcing.
# Does not affect Telegram link-intent JWTs. Clear or lower this value if you lock yourself out during testing.
# REXALGO_SESSION_MIN_IAT=1745600000

# Postgres connection string. For local dev with docker-compose.dev.yml use:
#   postgres://rexalgo:rexalgo@127.0.0.1:5432/rexalgo
# On Railway set this to the provided Postgres URL.
DATABASE_URL=postgres://rexalgo:rexalgo@127.0.0.1:5432/rexalgo

# Postgres pool size per replica. Default 25 (up from 10) so one API instance
# can serve ~500 concurrent users without queueing for connections. Budget:
# 5 replicas × 25 = 125 total; keep it well under Postgres `max_connections`.
# PGPOOL_MAX=25

# Optional: Railway pre-deploy can still run `npm run migrate` before the new
# container starts (faster first request). The API always runs migrate again on
# first `ensureDbReady()` — it is a no-op when already applied — so a failed
# pre-deploy cannot strand you on an old schema.

# Per-user concurrent backtest cap. Default 3 — set lower if backtests start to
# saturate the API or higher if you are comfortable with users spending more CPU.
# REXALGO_MAX_CONCURRENT_BACKTESTS_PER_USER=3

# Optional but strongly recommended in production: shared Redis for cross-instance
# state (webhook rate limits today; session cache later). Without it we fall back
# to an in-process Map which is fine for a single API instance but lets each
# replica enforce the 120 req/min webhook budget separately. `redis://` for
# plaintext, `rediss://` for TLS.
# REDIS_URL=redis://127.0.0.1:6379

# One-shot wipe of all app rows (users, strategies, Telegram tokens, …).
# From `backend/`: REXALGO_CONFIRM_FLUSH_ALL_APP_DATA=yes npm run db:flush
# Never set in normal server env — run manually in Railway shell when needed.
# REXALGO_CONFIRM_FLUSH_ALL_APP_DATA=yes

# Admin allowlist. Comma-separated emails that can access /admin and approve master-studio requests.
# Example: ADMIN_EMAILS=jm@rexalgo.xyz,ops@rexalgo.xyz
ADMIN_EMAILS=
# Optional direct Telegram fan-out for admins (comma-separated chat IDs).
# Use this when you want admin alerts even before account-linking Telegram in-app.
# You can get your chat id by messaging @userinfobot in Telegram.
# ADMIN_TELEGRAM_CHAT_IDS=123456789,987654321

# Public origin of the Next API (no trailing slash). Used for full webhook URLs in:
# - Master studio (/copy-trading/studio)
# - Strategy studio (/marketplace/studio)
# - TV Webhooks (/tv-webhooks)
# Production: set to your branded API host (e.g. https://api.rexalgo.xyz), NOT the
# Vercel frontend origin. If unset, studios may fall back to the default deploy URL
# (e.g. *.railway.app), which still works but exposes your hosting provider in copied links.
# Local dev with external bots: tunnel to Next (port 3000), e.g. https://abc123.ngrok-free.app
# PUBLIC_API_URL=

# Legacy alias for PUBLIC_API_URL — still read for backward compatibility.
# Also used as fallback for Telegram OAuth redirect Location when
# X-Forwarded-Host is missing (Vercel → Railway). Set to SPA origin, e.g.:
# PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://rexalgo.xyz
# PUBLIC_APP_URL=

# If PUBLIC_APP_URL points at the API host for webhooks, set the SPA origin here
# so Telegram OAuth redirects still land on the site users open:
# REXALGO_PUBLIC_BROWSER_ORIGIN=https://rexalgo.xyz

# Telegram login + notifications.
# Create a bot via @BotFather, paste token here. Username is without @.
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# TELEGRAM_BOT_USERNAME=
#
# Shared secret the bot sends with every webhook delivery as
# `X-Telegram-Bot-Api-Secret-Token`. Used by `/api/telegram/webhook` to reject
# spoofed updates. Any 1-256 char ASCII string of `A-Z a-z 0-9 _ -`; generate
# one with `openssl rand -hex 32`. Register it with:
#   curl -X POST "https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/setWebhook" \
#     -d "url=https://api.rexalgo.xyz/api/telegram/webhook" \
#     -d "secret_token=<TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET>"
# TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
#
# Dev-only: skip the webhook secret check (useful when tunnelling a local
# bot through ngrok before calling setWebhook). NEVER set in production.
# REXALGO_TELEGRAM_ALLOW_UNSIGNED=1
#
# Optional: log telegram user id + auth_date after successful widget verify (stdout).
# REXALGO_TELEGRAM_TRACE=1

# Optional: session cookie path (default /api — cookie not sent on non-/api paths)
# REXALGO_SESSION_COOKIE_PATH=/api

# Optional: session cookie Domain (e.g. .rexalgo.xyz). If unset and PUBLIC_APP_URL
# is set, Domain is derived so cookies work when the API is behind Vercel→Railway.
# REXALGO_SESSION_COOKIE_DOMAIN=.rexalgo.xyz

# Optional: browser session length (JWT + cookie), in days. Default 90 (matches Mudrex key lifetime cap), max 90.
# Use a lower value (e.g. 7) if you want shorter-lived browser cookies for shared machines.
# REXALGO_SESSION_MAX_AGE_DAYS=90

# Optional: session cookie SameSite policy. Defaults to `strict` which
# eliminates CSRF on any accidental GET-mutation handler. Set to `lax` if a
# post-login navigation turns out to strip the cookie in production (no known
# case today — all API calls go through fetch()). `none` requires Secure=true.
# REXALGO_SESSION_SAMESITE=strict

# Optional: internal base URL for historical OHLC (strategy simulations). Default is suitable for dev.
# REXALGO_OHLC_API_BASE=https://api.example.com

# ─── Mudrex client-side rate limiter (backend/src/lib/mudrexRateLimit.ts) ───
# All values are per Mudrex API key. Defaults match the Mudrex v1.0.5 docs
# exactly: https://docs.trade.mudrex.com/docs/authentication-rate-limits
# Tighten (lower) them if you see upstream 429s under bursty traffic.
#
# Enhanced-tier endpoints: create order, cancel order, add-margin, riskorder
# (POST/PATCH), reverse, partial close, close, get/set leverage.
# MUDREX_RL_ENHANCED_PER_SEC=5
# MUDREX_RL_ENHANCED_PER_MIN=125
# MUDREX_RL_ENHANCED_PER_HOUR=2500
# MUDREX_RL_ENHANCED_PER_DAY=25000
#
# Standard-tier endpoints: wallet, transfer, assets list/detail, open/history
# orders, open/history positions, futures funds, liq-price.
# MUDREX_RL_STANDARD_PER_SEC=2
# MUDREX_RL_STANDARD_PER_MIN=50
# MUDREX_RL_STANDARD_PER_HOUR=1000
# MUDREX_RL_STANDARD_PER_DAY=10000
#
# Max time the limiter will queue a request before returning 429
# MUDREX_RATE_LIMIT. Interactive = user-facing API routes; background =
# copy-mirror loop, TV webhooks, asset pagination.
# MUDREX_RL_MAX_WAIT_INTERACTIVE_MS=3000
# MUDREX_RL_MAX_WAIT_BACKGROUND_MS=60000
